         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">86/07/26 ¶  ¶ I was pleasingly surprised, dear Dr Beccari, to receive together  ¶ two ¶  parts of your admirable "Malesia" by last mail, ¶  and beg to thank you for your generous sending; it will be f...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.07.26c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">86/07/26</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I was pleasingly surprised, dear Dr Beccari, to receive together <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">two</hi>
               </seg> parts of your admirable "Malesia" by last mail,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90): last part of vol. 2 and first part of vol. 3; see M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 26 July 1886 (in this edition as 86-07-26b).</p>
               </note> and beg to thank you for your generous sending; it will be for my private library, but I always order also a copy through Dulan &amp; Co for my Department, so that I have tw[o]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg>: MS damaged. All [ ] <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in the letter have this meaning.</p>
               </note> sets of this important work. Your learned es[say] on the ant-plants h[as] now come to a worth[y] conclusion.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am not surprised [that] our friend Baron C[esati] and myself have [not al]ways recognized the [New] Guinea ferns with absolute correctness, or viewed them in Hookers and Bakers limitation.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M's main treatment of the Papuan ferns is in B76.12.03, pp 76–82. See also W. Hooker &amp; Baker (1865-68) and later editions (see TL2, publication No. 3024).</p>
               </note> Indeed Darwinism leads to Jordanism! (entre nous).<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'Critical botany … has … been exaggerated by Alexis Jordan and his followers into an impracticable and futile extreme' (B. Jackson (1881), p. xxxviii). But see notes to M to W. Thiselton-Dyer, 25 July 1885.</p>
               </note> — Both Cesati and myself may in some cases have trusted too implicitly to incorrectly named Asiatic and other specimens of ferns in our collections for comparison. At the whole, he as well as I, have come fairly near the truth in our identifications. — But you will wonder why I did not, when resuming the "Papuan Plants" for elaborating the plants of Capt Everills &amp; Mr Forbes's Expeditions refer to Cesati's memoir.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Cesati (1877). M resumed his series on Papuan plants in B85.06.03. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This is easily ex[plained ….]<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/> […] in this paragraph and the next indicates missing text, where the corner of MS is missing.</p>
               </note> published D'Alber[tis …] towards the end o[f …] and Cesati publis[hed …] in Febr <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">1877</hi>
               </seg>. — In […] I explored at Shar[k Bay…] and in other parts […] Australia;<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M visited WA, including Shark's Bay, in 1877.</p>
               </note> and th[…] essay of our lamen[ted …] must have come, w[…] I was away. In all […]lity, when among th[…] of accumulated prints on my return I glanced merely on the "Prospetto", I was <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">misled</hi>
               </seg> by the word "Polinesia" in the title, as New Guinea is not strictly Polynesian. Soon after in 1877 I became <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">very ill,</hi>
               </seg> for a long time, in 1878 I moved into new quarters with library &amp;c &amp;c; — in 1879 we had to commence the heavy extra-work for the [… Melb]ourne exhibition<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1880-1.</p>
               </note> [… i]n which also Italy [… sp]lendidly represented. [… los]t sight of the "Prospetto" […]ur, and <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">hunted </hi>
               </seg>it […] <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">now</hi>
               </seg>, when I saw […]oted by Baker<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Baker (1886). </p>
               </note> and […]elf in the 3th<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>3 <seg style="font-style: italic; ">over</seg> 5.</p>
               </note> vol […M]alesia. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I shall cer[tainly] explain this unin[tentio]nal shortcoming in the forthcoming (almost <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ready</hi>
               </seg>) 9th number of the Papuan Plants.<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B90.05.01. M did not mention Cesati in the introduction to this part, which did not contain any ferns.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Before I leave this subject I like to remark, that I by no means concur in all the limitations of our friend Baker, who likes to keep up <name key="Nephrodium">Nephrodium</name>, <name key="Nephrolepis">Nephrolepis</name>, <name key="Gymnogramme">Gymnogramme</name> in due piety to Hooker senior though we should "numquam in verba magistri jurare"<note xml:id="ftn12" type="footnote" n="12">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Never swear by the words of the master.</p>
               </note> — Exempli causa take <name key="Schizaea%20dichotoma">Schizaea dichotoma</name>; how can be united to it S. Forsteri, which both Sprengel and Willdenow clearly defined in the beginning of the century. As Mr Baker never saw a[…] Schizea in a wild sta[te] he may be easily misl[ed] though S. Forsteri be[longs] almost to the section [Ac]tinostachys, as I poin[ted out] in Campbell's "New [Hebri]des",<note xml:id="ftn13" type="footnote" n="13">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B73.13.01, p. 27. The point was not made explicitly, but implied by the discussion.</p>
               </note> of which work I […] gave you a copy. — It will be worth your while, [to in]vestigate this Sch[izea] question independen[tly] in Italy; the two c[…] distinguished at a glance! but S. bifida is only a small form of S. dichotoma, as any one can see on the heathground near Melbourne. Kindly tell me the results of <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">your</hi>
               </seg> examination, as this matter should be cleared up, after the error has been continued in the Malesia.<note xml:id="ftn14" type="footnote" n="14">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90), vol. 3, p. 52. In M's copy of the work, now in the library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne, he has written an emphatic 'No!' at the point where <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Schizaea%20dichotoma">Schizaea dichotoma</name>
                     </seg> and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. Forsteri</seg> are united.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will at last receive the volume on "Myoporinous plants" with 76 quarto-plates, its issue being long delayed at the binders establishment.<note xml:id="ftn15" type="footnote" n="15">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B86.08.05. The indexes list 72 numbered plates plus two supplemental plates, consistent with the content of copies seen.</p>
               </note> The incessant demands [y]ear after year on my Department for the successive great Exhibitions,<note xml:id="ftn16" type="footnote" n="16">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Gillbank (2008).</p>
               </note> has much hindered my Museum-work; but the sorting of spare specimens is now under progress, and you will therefore soon get something in return for your Sumatran plants.<note xml:id="ftn17" type="footnote" n="17">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to O. Beccari, 5 February 1880.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>And now my dear Dr Becari, I bid you "adieu" — I am suffering much from pulmonary inflammation, and even if that does not carry me off soon, — at best there can be little time left of my earthly career! If I can identify my name yet with some Papuan plants I shall be thankful to my generous friends like your self and then my bid<note xml:id="ftn18" type="footnote" n="18">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>bit?</p>
               </note> of earthly task <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">is done</hi>
               </seg>!</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Your <name key="Agapetes">Agapetes</name> seem to me deserving a distinct generic place; the biformous anthers are quite peculiar, so far as my researches go, and bring them near <name key="Macleania">Macleania</name> Can you kindly tell me the year, when Marsigli<note xml:id="ftn19" type="footnote" n="19">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marsili? Marsili (1786).</p>
               </note> published <name key="Firmiana">Firmiana</name>, a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">good</hi>
               </seg> genus. How can species with superior and inferior radicle be put into <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">one</hi>
               </seg> genus!</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>What a <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">pity</hi>
               </seg> that Baker made a new fern genus on so trifling ground; the difference is not such as between <name key="Alsophila">Alsophila</name> and <name key="Polypodium">Polypodium</name>.<note xml:id="ftn20" type="footnote" n="20">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the centre margin between pp. 2 and 3, adjacent to the end of the discussion on p. 2 of Cesati's and M's treatment of ferns. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Triphlebia</seg> was erected in Beccari (1877-90), vol. 3, p. 41.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I notice a printing error, Angiopteris <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">erecta</hi>
               </seg> instead evecta<note xml:id="ftn21" type="footnote" n="21">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the margin of p. 5. </p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best salutation to Signor D'Albertis<note xml:id="ftn22" type="footnote" n="22">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the margin of p. 7; almost certainly Luigi Maria d'Albertis.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
